message.content:
1. The intervention took place in 2012.
2. After the intervention, the proportion of households who purchased anti-mosquito products in the last month was 47.8% in intervention clusters.
3. The number of households in the intervention clusters was 5293.
4. The number of households who purchased anti-mosquito products in the intervention clusters was 2503.
5. After the intervention, the proportion of households who purchased anti-mosquito products in the last month was 53.3% in control clusters.
6. The number of households in the control clusters was 5079.
7. The number of households who purchased anti-mosquito products in the control clusters was 2707.
8. The difference in the proportion of households who purchased anti-mosquito products between intervention and control clusters was -0.05.
9. The 95% confidence interval for the difference in the proportion of households who purchased anti-mosquito products between intervention and control clusters was -0.100 to -0.010.

messages.content:
Statement: In 2012, after the intervention, the proportion of households who purchased anti-mosquito products in the last month was significantly lower in intervention clusters (47.8%; 2503/5293) than in control clusters (53.3%; 2707/5079) (difference − 0.05, 95% CIca −0.100 to −0.010).
